##On the first day of the Lunar New Year, they relay 29 hours of food to Hubei Hospital | prism

Micro-signal Lengjing

Feature Introduction, tencent news product column, "Prism" focus on financial in-depth reports.

By Peric Lee
Production | prism tencent Xiaoman studio

Welcome to download tencent news APP for more quality information

January 25th, just after 16:00, the first day of the Lunar New Year. The Hubei Huangshi Central Hospital and the Daye People's Hospital placed two orders for rice, noodles, cooking oil, water and beverages, and dry adjustment.

In previous years, many hospitalized patients will go home, this year is not the same, many patients, doctors are also on duty, urgent logistics and material support. But the arrival of rice, grain and oil on time, the hospital procurement staff do not know: Because the entire region's operation, including transportation logistics has been affected by the epidemic.

Tan Dexiao, a young man born in the 1990s, was the truck driver in charge of transporting the two orders.

He had planned that although this task was extremely important, it would not be a problem to deliver it on time: In his experience, the delivery from Wuhan to these two hospitals was not too far away, and three hours would be enough if he took the expressway normally, even if he took the national highway, time should also be in time, do not delay the use of the hospital.

Unexpectedly, it took 29 hours.

A 29-hour relay race

Tan Dexiao is an employee of American food, and the one who takes that order is a big customer of American food, Wuhan Yi Cang.

Many take-out parties rely on American food, even if they may not know the name. American cuisine is one of the largest food distribution suppliers in China, supplying nearly 3 million restaurants. American cuisine is also Wuhan East Lake District to attract investment enterprises, in 2019 entered the optical valley.

The first day is a major customer of American Food Wuhan a Warehouse Manager Zhao Xiaofeng on duty. It looks like a hospital order. He's got an emergency pick-up line. Only two hours, 6 tons of supplies ready; 19 o'clock, loaded, the driver is Tan Dexiao.

Not Wanting to leave the doctor and his patients hungry the next day, he decided to take the night route and make a detour around the China National Highway 107. His plan is to first deliver the People's Hospital of Daye, and then to the Central Hospital of Huangshi, a distance of 175 km.

The ingredients are in the truck

It was raining and driving on a rainy night. Tan went to the junction of Ezhou and Daye and found that the road had been cut off to prevent the spread of the disease.

Tan Dexiao was quite anxious, would like to from the side of the barrier around, did not think of the rain mud, heavy trucks, stuck in the roadside soft roadbed. As a result, the entire van tilted, one rear wheel stuck in the soft mud.

Tan DEXIAO got out of the car to work, but also fell into a puddle, clothes and shoes are wet. It was only two or three degrees, and the People's Hospital in Daye, which was in dire need of supplies, was 40 kilometers away.

At this time, is the New Year's Day at 9:00 pm, from Tan dexiao departure only more than two hours.

Tan Dexiao also dare not leave the car, while contact rescue, while guarding supplies.

At the same time, in the rear, company colleagues, cold chain supervisor Yang Jun got the news, while contacting the hospital, explain the accident, apologize to the hospital logistics personnel for understanding; also rushed to the car to help rescue. But by this time there were more road closures, and Yang Jun had taken both roads under new barricades, walking nearly 100 kilometers back and forth in vain, anxious.

After 11 pm, the second colleague driver often joint relay to help.

Master Chang was at home that day. The trucks were parked in the warehouse. After hearing this, I immediately took Tan dexiao clothes, pack biscuits, boiled eggs, hot water, hurried to the warehouse, driving the second van set out.

The roads are slippery at night, with dirt washed down from the mountains, and the 70-kilometer road often takes two hours to get there.

It was a little after 1:00 a.m. on the second day of the New Year. To make matters worse, there were new roadblocks, and Chang's van was forced to stop 3.9 km from Tan.

Late winter rainy night, no flashlight, often combined with a mobile phone lighting, navigation, hiking back clothes and food, and finally meet Tan Dexiao.

In the middle of the night, the rescue vehicles could not come, and the two spent the night in the cab without air conditioning.

On the morning of the 2nd day of the Lunar New Year, nearby villagers found a truck stuck in the mud. Xiao Tan and Lao Chang were touched by the warm-hearted people who immediately brought them food, clothes, shoes and cigarettes from their homes. Knowing that the truck was going to the hospital to deliver supplies, the village and township cadres in the vicinity immediately decided to clear the obstacles, and the rescue crane was able to enter.

On the afternoon of the second day of the Lunar New Year, this truckload of supplies was hoisted out, and Tan Dexiao was finally able to start driving again.

Screenshots of Tan dexiao's wechat account and friends'circle

At 23:44 on January 26, after 29 hours, the rice flour oil was delivered to the Puoi Hospital district of Huangshi Central Hospital.

Later, the Huangshi Central Hospital coordinated with the local government to issue special permits for American food delivery vehicles during the epidemic period, which allowed them to travel on special high-speed routes and reduced travel time.

After the delivery of the second hospital goods, January 27, the evening of the third day of the Lunar New Year, Tan dexiao safe return to Wuhan.

On This Day, Dori Tandexiao suffered a lot, but he didn't think of complaining, and was even a little embarrassed. After the truck was rescued in the afternoon of the second day of the eighth lunar month, most of his colleagues didn't realize the difficulty of the trip, "We were too embarrassed to talk about it until the car was saved. "

150 employees of Hubei Hospital

A full 48 hours later, Tan Dexiao finally had a hot meal prepared by his colleagues. Tan dexiao's colleague in Wuhan, Yang Jun, who was the first one to drive to help on the first night of the first day, was also relieved: "although the twists and turns, people, cars, goods arrived safely, I can be a little relieved. "

My colleagues have been busy.

On January 26, on Tan Dexiao's way to Huangshi Hospital, the Wuhan Union Hospital and Wuhan People's Hospital both placed orders for tens of thousands of yuan worth of supplies, about three days'worth of goods, including rice, meat, water, frozen goods and spices.

Nearly a week, the United States has been delivered to a number of hospitals in Wuhan Rice and flour oil, milk drinks, dry, eggs, meat and poultry and vegetables, such as the accumulation of nearly 100,000 Jin. Currently, hospitals in Hubei Province that place orders for American cuisine are: Wuhan Union Hospital, People's Hospital of Wuhan University, Huangshi Central Hospital, Puai Hospital district of Huangshi Central Hospital, Daye People's Hospital, Hubei 672 integrated Chinese and Western Medicine Orthopedic Hospital, etc. .

In Wuhan area, there are about 150 employees participating in the "Spring Festival is not closed" , including 40 people in the warehouse, 90-100 drivers, and about 20 on-duty managers. Not only hospitals, but they also deliver food to restaurants, cafeterias, and other customers throughout the region.

Tan dexiao is oneself sign up"do not close"of:"should not all come out with benefit, take voluntary (sign up to deliver) . I'm willing to sign up. There are so many people on the line, and I want to help. It's not that I'm a personal hero, but I do want to contribute. I can donate."

Not only Tan Dexiao, a number of drivers are willing to stick to their posts to ensure delivery.

Many of them are uncommunicative, and in the group of six warehouses in Wuhan, a few words can express their attitude ——"I can go out tomorrow" .

Despite the risks, the drivers said they were willing to help with the delivery of food to their compatriots who were fighting the epidemic. On the other hand, hospitals were prepared to send protective clothing to the drivers and put on their clothes to deliver food to the logistics kitchen area.

For the health of front-line employees, but also for food safety, American food on the way to do enough safety protection. From security check in warehouse to sorting and distribution, all production workshops are also strictly disinfected many times a day, warehouse staff take body temperature twice a day, and drivers enter the warehouse to take temperature in a unified way, daily issue of updated medical masks and hand sanitizer for drivers.

At present, they are coordinating with relevant departments in Hubei, starting from January 27, through its own procurement system, logistics and distribution system for Hubei hospitals, garrisons, epidemic prevention support units, Epidemic Prevention Command institutions and other first-line departments to provide food distribution.

Screen capture of truck drivers

The drivers'comments came as a surprise to management, including Jiangchuan District, senior vice president of American cuisine, and touched the hearts of their employees. He told prism that at present, there are a few core hospitals in Wuhan among the users of American food distribution. It's a heavy job.

About upstream purchase, at present, they and Unilever, Nestle, Wudeli flour and other suppliers in hundreds of close cooperation, to maximize to meet the needs of users.

This year's situation is very special, as the spread of the epidemic, the United States food observed that up to 17 on the 23rd, Wuhan United States food orders and transactions were 30% more than the previous day.

Wenzhengyi, general manager of Wuhan, an American dish, said: "It may be that fewer and fewer fresh suppliers are sticking to their business and the demand for take-out food is increasing, leading to an increase in the demand for orders. " "As long as there are restaurant orders, as long as take-out food is taken, Wuhan cuisine will ensure normal distribution. "

More fresh food is heading for Wuhan families

Normal Distribution, and in the midst of an epidemic, a bunch of ordinary people have to work even harder to make that promise.

On January 26, two new cases were confirmed in Huzhou, Zhejiang, including one in Deqing County, Zhejiang.

This is the northern jurisdiction of Hangzhou, which happens to be in the town of Leidian, Deqing County, Zhejiang, just a few kilometers away from the newly confirmed case. Around 104, China National Highway 304 were affected by the road closure, the surrounding high-speed exits are gradually closed. However, as of 16:30 on the 26th, Hangzhou North under the number of restaurant merchants is more than 150, most of which are take-away merchants.

Road closure on a rainy night in Huzhou

That means thousands of families in Hangzhou will not be able to eat if the ingredients are not delivered, morning-harvest suppliers will no longer be able to deliver, fresh meat and poultry will be out of stock, and restaurants will be out of business.

Late that night, Hangzhou North district staff overnight road, country roads, national roads, high-speed visit one by one to find the truck can take the route.

Drivers have delivery vehicles, warehouse employees drive their own cars, and even ride electric bikes out all night.

It had also been raining for more than 20 days, and the roads were dark and slippery. In the first half of the night, they found two roads, until about two o'clock in the morning, there was another change and the national road was closed. The party set out again to explore the road, finally found a feasible route, are late at night.

Despite a lot of detour, but the final smooth distribution to 223 stores, no late, do not want to order takeout of the ordinary people hungry.

Shouguang Vegetable Farmers Help Wuhan by picking vegetables overnight

Previously, American cuisine mainly served restaurant merchants. This emergency outbreak caused many ordinary families to run short of food ingredients. The management decided that under the circumstances of ensuring the demand for food and take-out, the special period would be for families in major cities such as Wuhan, gradual opening of distribution services.

In Wuhan, the number of orders for us cuisine by households has continued to rise, with households accounting for 80 per cent of the types of users who placed orders with US cuisine only on January 26.

In accordance with the standards of health and epidemic prevention, for community users, unified distribution of American dishes to the community epidemic prevention duty point for home users to pick up. In addition to Wuhan, other cities around the United States food epidemic management, according to the local situation, gradually open to provide family distribution.

More fresh food is also heading to Wuhan, to ensure that ordinary families have food to eat.

On January 26, hundreds of tons of vegetables, including squash, potatoes, gluten-free beans and cucumbers, arrived from Chongqing to support Wuhan. These vegetables are sold at super-fair prices at Wu Shang, Zhong Bai and Zhong Shang.

On January 27, ele.me, in collaboration with the 10,000 tons supplier, organized the supply, in the Community Convenience Supermarket "Home" , "Today" and other established 100 fresh convenience service stations, and will further increase the site. Wuhan residents only need to be in 20:00 on the same day, through the hungry Moji order, buy fruits and vegetables, meat, poultry, eggs and milk and other commodities, the next day can go to the service station to pick up their own or ask delivery boy security door-to-door.

On January 28, the first batch of 350 tons of fresh vegetables from Shouguang, Shandong Province, will be donated to Wuhan free of charge. Shouguang will then provide 600 tonnes of quality and cheap vegetables a day for 10-15 days.

The New Year of 2020 is destined to be an extraordinary year, filled with anxiety and emotion. Although Tan said he never wanted to be a hero and only wanted to be ordinary and content, ordinary people do have a heroic side.

Shouguang Vegetable Farmers Help Wuhan by picking vegetables overnight

Previously, American cuisine mainly served restaurant merchants. This emergency outbreak caused many ordinary families to run short of food ingredients. The management decided that under the circumstances of ensuring the demand for food and take-out, the special period would be for families in major cities such as Wuhan, gradual opening of distribution services.

In Wuhan, the number of orders for us cuisine by households has continued to rise, with households accounting for 80 per cent of the types of users who placed orders with US cuisine only on January 26.

In accordance with the standards of health and epidemic prevention, for community users, unified distribution of American dishes to the community epidemic prevention duty point for home users to pick up. In addition to Wuhan, other cities around the United States food epidemic management, according to the local situation, gradually open to provide family distribution.

More fresh food is also heading to Wuhan, to ensure that ordinary families have food to eat.

On January 26, hundreds of tons of vegetables, including squash, potatoes, gluten-free beans and cucumbers, arrived from Chongqing to support Wuhan. These vegetables are sold at super-fair prices at Wu Shang, Zhong Bai and Zhong Shang.

On January 27, ele.me, in collaboration with the 10,000 tons supplier, organized the supply, in the Community Convenience Supermarket "Home" , "Today" and other established 100 fresh convenience service stations, and will further increase the site. Wuhan residents only need to be in 20:00 on the same day, through the hungry Moji order, buy fruits and vegetables, meat, poultry, eggs and milk and other commodities, the next day can go to the service station to pick up their own or ask delivery boy security door-to-door.

On January 28, the first batch of 350 tons of fresh vegetables from Shouguang, Shandong Province, will be donated to Wuhan free of charge. Shouguang will then provide 600 tonnes of quality and cheap vegetables a day for 10-15 days.

The New Year of 2020 is destined to be an extraordinary year, filled with anxiety and emotion. Although Tan said he never wanted to be a hero and only wanted to be ordinary and content, ordinary people do have a heroic side.
